# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dgx_timeseries_lab project-specific
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Top-level data/ directory holds large external artifacts that never get
# checked in — NAS-symlinked telemetry archives, NASA SMAP/MSL downloads,
# sneakernet-transferred LLM weights (Llama / Mistral GGUFs), and parquet
# outputs from `dgx-ts synth`. The leading slash is critical: it anchors
# the pattern at the repo root so it does NOT match the in-package
# `packages/dgx_ts_core/src/dgx_ts_core/data/` Python module (which holds
# the TelemetryWindow / Channel / Dataset Protocol code).
/data/

# Belt-and-suspenders: explicit allow rule for the in-package `data/`
# Python module. The anchored `/data/` rule above already spares it; this
# makes the intent obvious to future maintainers and protects against
# someone accidentally re-adding a bare `data/` line.
#
# NOTE: we DON'T add a parallel `!packages/**/datasets/**` rule — there
# was never a `datasets/` ignore to override, and the broad allow leaked
# __pycache__/ directories back into tracking. The original __pycache__/
# rule at the top of this file handles those without help.
!packages/**/data/
!packages/**/data/**

# Re-ignore build artifacts AFTER the allow rule above. Gitignore's
# "last matching rule wins" semantics means these need to come after the
# `!packages/**/data/**` allow to keep __pycache__/ and *.pyc out of
# tracking even inside the allowed in-package data/ paths.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[codz]

